@node "WORK" "How Final Typer Works"

HOW TO USE THIS PROGRAM
-----------------------
After  the  installing  process,  you  will  be able to run FinalTyper.  Select
"Final  Typer"  from  the  "USER"  menu  and wait for its loading up.  A little
window will pop up.
Final Typer has 7 gadgets: 6 buttons and one Integer gadget.
Clicking  on the button will allow you accessing another window which will hold
all  chars FinalTyper can insert inside your doc.  These chars are divided into
"arguments".   Clicking  upon  "A"  gadget will show you all "A"s-releted chars
(all  the  "a"s  with  accents), clicking on "E" will show you all "E"s-releted
chars and so on.
If  you  cannot find out a char inside "A" to "U" windows, try pressing the "X"
gadget  which  will  show  you  another list of gadgets (the so called "eXtreme
mess!!!" :)

The Integer gadget needs a further explanation. Pay attention!!!

Every  Final  Writer  text  window has its own ARexx port.  This port is called
FINALW.x  where  x  is  the  number  of  the window and ranges from 1 to n.  At
startup, Final Writer opens just ONE window, so you could access it by ARexx as
"FINALW.1"  and  also  FinalTyper  will work fine at startup.  But, if you open
another  window  it will be called "FINALW.2" and if you desire to type in some
chars using FinalTyper IT WON'T WORK!!!

Ok, ok... don't be afraid. Everything is under control... don't be afraid.

The  solution is the Integer Gadget.  Just insert inside it the window you wish
to insert chars to and everything will work fine.

@endnode

